+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. The reopened fallback regression was addressed once in the shared fix above, so there is no separate code path to change for this thread.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread points at an outdated hunk, and reviving a legacy preview branch on the current branch would go in the wrong direction. The fix keeps the current normalization path and does not reintroduce legacy preview branching.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Added the requested regression coverage in [tests/test_preview.py](/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260424T000621Z_z614nofg/20260424T000621Z-v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/tests/test_preview.py:31). The new test exercises `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state=\"manual_review\"` and verifies the fallback payload stays normalized to `human_review_required` with `requires_human_review=True`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Updated the fallback example in [docs/approval_policy.md](/var/folders/xc/sy7ktq0n42d1n78zg10b8p_r0000gn/T/pr-review-fanout-remediation_20260424T000621Z_z614nofg/20260424T000621Z-v5-recovery-in-thread-run1/workspace/docs/approval_policy.md:9) so the documented payload now includes `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
